def: Pain in the muscles; muscular rheumatism or neuralgia.
An ornamented cake distributed among friends or visitors on thefestival of Twelfth-night.
Winding around something; twisting; embracing; climbing bywinding about a support; as, the hop is a twinning plant.
To diminish the quantity of; to disquantity. [Obs.] Sir T.Browne.
Any one of three species of Australian burrowing marsupials ofthe genus Phascolomys, especially the common species (P. ursinus).They are nocturnal in their habits, and feed mostly on roots.
Having a small, distinct point; apiculate. Henslow.
Made in form; ceremonious; as, solemn war; conforming with alllegal requirements; as, probate in solemn form. Burrill. Jarman.Greenleaf. Solemn League and Covenant. See Covenant, 2.
Pertaining to, of the nature of, or characterized by,intercession or entreaty.
Divination by the entrails of human being.
